ltmRateFilterCname.description: The rate class name specified by the user according to the same syntax allowed for rules or pool names

ltmRateFilterRate.name: ltmRateFilterRate
ltmRateFilterRate.description: The base rate. It is a number which may be postfixed with a metric of either bps, Kbps or Mbps, to indicate bits per second, Kilobits per second, or Megabits per second, respectively. Note: these numbers are powers of 10, not powers of 2. If no postfix is specified, the number is interpreted as bps. The rate specifies the maximum throughput to allot to traffic handled by the Rate Class. Packets in excess of the posted rate will be dropped.

ltmRateFilterCeil.name: ltmRateFilterCeil
ltmRateFilterCeil.description: The ceiling rate. It is defined like the base rate, but specifies how far beyond the base rate the traffic is allowed to flow when bursting (details on bursting below). The ceiling rate is an absolute limit - it is impossible for traffic to flow at a higher rate than the ceiling rate, even when bursting. If the ceiling rate is omitted or is equal to the base rate, the traffic may not exceed the base rate. It is illegal for the ceiling rate to be less than the base rate.

ltmRateFilterBurst.name: ltmRateFilterBurst
ltmRateFilterBurst.description: The burst size. It specifies the maximum number of bytes the traffic is allowed to burst when exceeding the base rate. The burst size is measured in bytes. If omitted, a default burst size is 0.

ltmRateFilterPname.name: ltmRateFilterPname
ltmRateFilterPname.description: The parent rate class name. It indicates that the rate class is a child of the named parent. Any child rate class has the ability to borrow bandwidth from its parent. (Borrowing is a feature which allows a child to burst even beyond the burst size by borrowing from the burst size of a parent.) If omitted, the rate class is not a child, but may be a parent if another rate class refers to it as such.

ltmRateFilterQtype.name: ltmRateFilterQtype
ltmRateFilterQtype.description: The queue discipline type. none - invalid state; sfq - stochastic fair queue; pfifo - priority FIFO.

ltmRateFilterDirection.name: ltmRateFilterDirection
ltmRateFilterDirection.description: The state of the direction which the filter shapes traffic to. any - shape to the client and server; client - only shape traffic to the client; server - only shape traffic to the server.

ltmRateFilterStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmRateFilterStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmPoolMinActiveMembers.name: ltmPoolMinActiveMembers
ltmPoolMinActiveMembers.description: The minimum number of active members required for traffic to be sent to the specified pool. This feature is used for priority pools. The minimum active members take into account both the status of the pool member (up/down) as well as the number of connections present on the pool member. If the number of active members falls below this given threshold, traffic is sent to the next priority pool.

ltmFastL4ProfileRttFromClient.name: ltmFastL4ProfileRttFromClient
ltmFastL4ProfileRttFromClient.description: The option to use TCP timestamp options to measure the round trip time to the client.

ltmFastL4ProfileRttFromServer.name: ltmFastL4ProfileRttFromServer
ltmFastL4ProfileRttFromServer.description: The option to use TCP timestamp options to measure the round trip time to the server.

ltmFastL4ProfileTcpCloseTimeout.name: ltmFastL4ProfileTcpCloseTimeout
ltmFastL4ProfileTcpCloseTimeout.description: The number of seconds without traffic before a connection in the FIN received state is eligible for deletion. This is only used when ltmFastL4ProfileLooseInitiation or ltmFastL4ProfileLooseClose is enabled.

ltmFastL4ProfileLooseInitiation.name: ltmFastL4ProfileLooseInitiation
ltmFastL4ProfileLooseInitiation.description: The option to allow any TCP packet to initiate a connection (rather than requiring a SYN.

ltmFastL4ProfileLooseClose.name: ltmFastL4ProfileLooseClose
ltmFastL4ProfileLooseClose.description: The option to aggressively close out a connection by allowing TMM to switch the ltmFastL4ProfileIdleTimeout to ltmFastL4ProfileTcpCloseTimeout once the first FIN packet has been seen.

ltmFastL4ProfileHardSyncookie.name: ltmFastL4ProfileHardSyncookie
ltmFastL4ProfileHardSyncookie.description: The option to enable hardware SYN cookie protection using Packet Velocity ASIC (PVA).

ltmFastL4ProfileSoftSyncookie.name: ltmFastL4ProfileSoftSyncookie
ltmFastL4ProfileSoftSyncookie.description: The state indicating whether or not software SYN cookie protection is enable.

ltmFastL4ProfileLateBinding.name: ltmFastL4ProfileLateBinding
ltmFastL4ProfileLateBinding.description: The state indicating whether or not Late Binding is enabled.

ltmFastL4ProfileExplicitFlowMigration.name: ltmFastL4ProfileExplicitFlowMigration
ltmFastL4ProfileExplicitFlowMigration.description: The state indicating whether connections are automatically migrated into the hardware (false) or whether they must be explicitly migrated to hardware by the iRule command BIGTCP::release_flow (true).

ltmFastL4ProfileClientTimeout.name: ltmFastL4ProfileClientTimeout
ltmFastL4ProfileClientTimeout.description: The number of seconds allowed for a client to transmit enough data to select a server when late binding is enabled.

ltmFastL4ProfileTimeoutRecovery.name: ltmFastL4ProfileTimeoutRecovery
ltmFastL4ProfileTimeoutRecovery.description: The action to take when late binding timeout occurs on a connection.

ltmHttpProfileHeaderInsert.description: The header to be inserted into the HTTP header for the specified HTTP profile.

ltmHttpProfileHeaderErase.name: ltmHttpProfileHeaderErase
ltmHttpProfileHeaderErase.description: The header to be erased into the HTTP header for the specified HTTP profile.

ltmHttpProfileFallbackHost.name: ltmHttpProfileFallbackHost
ltmHttpProfileFallbackHost.description: The fallback host name used in HTTP redirect for the specified HTTP profile.

ltmHttpProfileCompressMode.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressMode
ltmHttpProfileCompressMode.description: Deprecated! The state that specifies whether compression is enabled.

ltmHttpProfileCompressMinSize.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressMinSize
ltmHttpProfileCompressMinSize.description: Deprecated! The value that specifies the minimum length of the server responses (in bytes) to be considered acceptable for compression.

ltmHttpProfileCompressBufferSize.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressBufferSize
ltmHttpProfileCompressBufferSize.description: Deprecated! The value that specifies the maximum number of uncompressed bytes that the compression proxy will buffer before it decides whether or not to compress the server's response, in case the server's response headers don't specify the content length of the response.

ltmHttpProfileCompressVaryHeader.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressVaryHeader
ltmHttpProfileCompressVaryHeader.description: Deprecated! The state that specifies whether to insert the header 'Vary: Accept-Encoding' in the server response for responses that have been compressed. If the 'Vary:' header already exists in the server response, then the value 'Accept-Encoding' will be appended to it.

ltmHttpProfileCompressAllowHttp10.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressAllowHttp10
ltmHttpProfileCompressAllowHttp10.description: Deprecated! The state that specifies whether to allow compression on responses to HTTP 1.0 requests.

ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipMemlevel.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipMemlevel
ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipMemlevel.description: Deprecated! The amount of memory that the proxy will use when doing compression. It must be an integer no less than 1 and no greater than 9. Higher values produce faster compression at the expense of more memory usage. The default memory level will be 8.

ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipWindowsize.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipWindowsize
ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipWindowsize.description: Deprecated! The number of bits in the window size that the compression proxy will use when compressing the server response. It should be an integer no less than 8 and no greater than 15. Higher values produce better compression ratios at the expense of more memory usage. The default window size will be 15.

ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipLevel.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipLevel
ltmHttpProfileCompressGzipLevel.description: Deprecated! The speed of compression that is applied to the response. Minimum value is 1, maximum is 9. The lower numbers give faster compression with lower ratios, and higher numbers give slower compression with higher ratios.

ltmHttpProfileCompressKeepAcceptEncoding.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressKeepAcceptEncoding
ltmHttpProfileCompressKeepAcceptEncoding.description: Deprecated! The state of the option to keep client-encoding header.

ltmHttpProfileCompressBrowserWorkarounds.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressBrowserWorkarounds
ltmHttpProfileCompressBrowserWorkarounds.description: Deprecated! The option to control whether or not to disable compression for known browsers that cannot handle certain types of compressed responses properly. If it's true, compression for known browsers will be disabled.

ltmHttpProfileResponseChunking.name: ltmHttpProfileResponseChunking
ltmHttpProfileResponseChunking.description: The HTTP chunk mode for the responses.

ltmHttpProfileLwsMaxColumn.name: ltmHttpProfileLwsMaxColumn
ltmHttpProfileLwsMaxColumn.description: The linear white space maximum column sizes used to support multi-line header insertion.

ltmHttpProfileLwsSeparator.name: ltmHttpProfileLwsSeparator
ltmHttpProfileLwsSeparator.description: The linear white space separator strings for the specified HTTP profile.

ltmHttpProfileRedirectRewrite.name: ltmHttpProfileRedirectRewrite
ltmHttpProfileRedirectRewrite.description: The HTTP redirect/rewrite mode for the responses.

ltmHttpProfileMaxHeaderSize.name: ltmHttpProfileMaxHeaderSize
ltmHttpProfileMaxHeaderSize.description: The maximum size of the headers.

ltmHttpProfilePipelining.name: ltmHttpProfilePipelining
ltmHttpProfilePipelining.description: Deprecated! The state indicating whether pipelining is enabled for this profile.

ltmHttpProfileInsertXforwardedFor.name: ltmHttpProfileInsertXforwardedFor
ltmHttpProfileInsertXforwardedFor.description: The state indicating whether inserting X-Forwarded-For is enabled for this profile.

ltmHttpProfileMaxRequests.name: ltmHttpProfileMaxRequests
ltmHttpProfileMaxRequests.description: The maximum connection requests allowed. The connection will be forced closed when this limit is reached.

ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaver.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaver
ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaver.description: Deprecated! The state indicating whether CPU saving mode is enable or not when doing compression.

ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaverHigh.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaverHigh
ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaverHigh.description: Deprecated! The CPU saver high threshold. When CPU utilization exceeds this value, compression is switched to NULL compression.

ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaverLow.name: ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaverLow
ltmHttpProfileCompressCpusaverLow.description: Deprecated! The CPU saver low threshold. When CPU utilization drops below this value, compression is switched to full throttle.

ltmHttpProfileRamcacheObjectMaxSize.name: ltmHttpProfileRamcacheObjectMaxSize
ltmHttpProfileRamcacheObjectMaxSize.description: Deprecated! The maximum size limitation for cached object in bytes.

ltmHttpProfileRamcacheIgnoreClient.name: ltmHttpProfileRamcacheIgnoreClient
ltmHttpProfileRamcacheIgnoreClient.description: Deprecated! The state that Ram cache ignores client cache.

ltmHttpProfileRamcacheAgingRate.name: ltmHttpProfileRamcacheAgingRate
ltmHttpProfileRamcacheAgingRate.description: Deprecated! The aging rate for the RAM cache.

ltmHttpProfileRamcacheInsertAgeHeader.description: Deprecated! The mode that indicates whether to insert the Age headers for RAM cache.

ltmHttpProfileServerAgentName.description: The server header sent in responses that the BIG-IP itself generates. The default value is BigIP. If is no string is set as the value, then no server header will be added to such responses.

ltmHttpProfileStatPassthroughOversizeSer.name: ltmHttpProfileStatPassthroughOversizeServerHeaders

ltmPersistProfileMsrdpNoSessionDir.name: ltmPersistProfileMsrdpNoSessionDir
ltmPersistProfileMsrdpNoSessionDir.description: This object indicates MS terminal services has been configured without a session directory and causes the initial MSRDP connection to be load-balanced.

ltmPersistProfileMapProxies.name: ltmPersistProfileMapProxies
ltmPersistProfileMapProxies.description: This object indicates whether we should map known proxies when the persistence mode is src_addr.

ltmPersistProfileAcrossServices.name: ltmPersistProfileAcrossServices
ltmPersistProfileAcrossServices.description: This object indicates whether the persistence entries added under this profile are available across services.

ltmPersistProfileAcrossVirtuals.name: ltmPersistProfileAcrossVirtuals
ltmPersistProfileAcrossVirtuals.description: This object indicates whether the persistence entries added under this profile are available across virtuals.

ltmPersistProfileAcrossPools.name: ltmPersistProfileAcrossPools
ltmPersistProfileAcrossPools.description: This object indicates whether the persistence entries added under this profile are available across pools.

ltmPersistProfileUieRule.name: ltmPersistProfileUieRule
ltmPersistProfileUieRule.description: The rule name for UIE mode.

ltmPersistProfileSipInfo.name: ltmPersistProfileSipInfo
ltmPersistProfileSipInfo.description: The SIP header name for persisting in the specified profile.

ltmTcpProfileNumber.name: ltmTcpProfileNumber
ltmTcpProfileNumber.description: The number of ltmTcpProfile entries in the table.

ltmTcpProfileTable.name: ltmTcpProfileTable
ltmTcpProfileTable.description: A table containing information of TCP profile.

ltmTcpProfileName.name: ltmTcpProfileName
ltmTcpProfileName.description: The name of a TCP profile.

ltmTcpProfileConfigSource.name: ltmTcpProfileConfigSource
ltmTcpProfileConfigSource.description: The state that specifies whether this is a base/pre-configured profile or user defined profile.

ltmTcpProfileDefaultName.name: ltmTcpProfileDefaultName
ltmTcpProfileDefaultName.description: The name of the profile from which the specified profile derives its attribute default values.

ltmTcpProfileResetOnTimeout.name: ltmTcpProfileResetOnTimeout
ltmTcpProfileResetOnTimeout.description: The feature of reset for idle timeout. If true and a TCP connection exceeds its idle_timeout, send a reset in addition to deleting the connection.

ltmTcpProfileTimeWaitRecycle.name: ltmTcpProfileTimeWaitRecycle
ltmTcpProfileTimeWaitRecycle.description: Recycle connection when SYN is received in TIME-WAIT state.

ltmTcpProfileDelayedAcks.name: ltmTcpProfileDelayedAcks
ltmTcpProfileDelayedAcks.description: If true, Enable delayed ACK to allow coalescing of multiple ACK responses.

ltmTcpProfileProxyMss.name: ltmTcpProfileProxyMss
ltmTcpProfileProxyMss.description: Whether or not to proxy maximum segment size. If true, advertise the same mss to the server as was negotiated with the client.

ltmTcpProfileProxyOptions.name: ltmTcpProfileProxyOptions
ltmTcpProfileProxyOptions.description: Whether or not to proxy an option. If true, advertise an option (e.g. time-stamps) to the server only if it was negotiated with the client.

ltmTcpProfileProxyBufferLow.name: ltmTcpProfileProxyBufferLow
ltmTcpProfileProxyBufferLow.description: The proxy buffer level at which the receive window is opened.

ltmTcpProfileProxyBufferHigh.name: ltmTcpProfileProxyBufferHigh
ltmTcpProfileProxyBufferHigh.description: The proxy buffer level at which the receive window is closed.

ltmTcpProfileIdleTimeout.name: ltmTcpProfileIdleTimeout
ltmTcpProfileIdleTimeout.description: The number of seconds without traffic before a connection is eligible for deletion.

ltmTcpProfileTimeWaitTimeout.name: ltmTcpProfileTimeWaitTimeout
ltmTcpProfileTimeWaitTimeout.description: The milliseconds in TIME-WAIT before entering CLOSED state.

ltmTcpProfileFinWaitTimeout.name: ltmTcpProfileFinWaitTimeout
ltmTcpProfileFinWaitTimeout.description: The number of seconds to remain in FIN-WAIT or CLOSING state before giving up. Zero is forever (or until maxrtx of FIN).

ltmTcpProfileCloseWaitTimeout.name: ltmTcpProfileCloseWaitTimeout
ltmTcpProfileCloseWaitTimeout.description: The number of seconds to remain in LAST-ACK state before giving up. Zero is forever (or until maxrtx of FIN).

ltmTcpProfileKeepAliveInterval.name: ltmTcpProfileKeepAliveInterval
ltmTcpProfileKeepAliveInterval.description: Keep alive probe interval in milliseconds.

ltmTcpProfileSynMaxrtx.name: ltmTcpProfileSynMaxrtx
ltmTcpProfileSynMaxrtx.description: The maximum number of retransmissions of SYN segments.

ltmTcpProfileMaxrtx.name: ltmTcpProfileMaxrtx
ltmTcpProfileMaxrtx.description: The maximum number of retransmissions of data segments.

ltmTcpProfileIpTosToClient.name: ltmTcpProfileIpTosToClient
ltmTcpProfileIpTosToClient.description: The IP type of service set in packets sent to client. Default:None.

ltmTcpProfileLinkQosToClient.name: ltmTcpProfileLinkQosToClient
ltmTcpProfileLinkQosToClient.description: The link quality of service set in packets sent to client. Default:None.

ltmTcpProfileDeferredAccept.name: ltmTcpProfileDeferredAccept
ltmTcpProfileDeferredAccept.description: The state that if true, defers allocation of connection chain context until payload from client has been seen.

ltmTcpProfileSelectiveAcks.name: ltmTcpProfileSelectiveAcks
ltmTcpProfileSelectiveAcks.description: The state that if true, enable RFC2018 Selective Acknowledgements.

ltmTcpProfileEcn.name: ltmTcpProfileEcn
ltmTcpProfileEcn.description: The state that if true, enable RFC3168 Extended Congestion Notification (ECN).

ltmTcpProfileLimitedTransmit.name: ltmTcpProfileLimitedTransmit
ltmTcpProfileLimitedTransmit.description: The state that if true, enables support for RFC3042 Limited Transmit Recovery

ltmTcpProfileHighPerfTcpExt.name: ltmTcpProfileHighPerfTcpExt
ltmTcpProfileHighPerfTcpExt.description: Deprecated! Replaced by ltmTcpProfileTimestamps. The state that if true, enables support for RFC1323 timestamps and window scaling (high bandwidth TCP extensions).

ltmTcpProfileSlowStart.name: ltmTcpProfileSlowStart
ltmTcpProfileSlowStart.description: The state if true, enable TCP slow-start by default. We use RFC3390 to slow-start rather than traditional congestion avoidance mechanisms.

ltmTcpProfileBandwidthDelay.name: ltmTcpProfileBandwidthDelay
ltmTcpProfileBandwidthDelay.description: Deprecated! The state if true, attempt to calculate the optimal bandwidth to use to the peer based on throughput and round-trip time, and don't exceed it.

ltmTcpProfileNagle.name: ltmTcpProfileNagle
ltmTcpProfileNagle.description: The state if true, delay sending data < MSS in size unless all prior data has been ACKed. This leads to less in-flight small-data, and less chance for drops, but can harm interactivity. Named after Nagle's algorithm.

ltmTcpProfileAckOnPush.name: ltmTcpProfileAckOnPush
ltmTcpProfileAckOnPush.description: The state if true, data-bearing in-order TCP segments will elicit immediate ACKs from us if they have the PUSH flag set, regardless of the setting of the delayed-ack profile option.

ltmTcpProfileMd5Sig.name: ltmTcpProfileMd5Sig
ltmTcpProfileMd5Sig.description: The state if true, use RFC2385 TCP-MD5 signatures to protect TCP traffic against intermediate tampering.

ltmTcpProfileMd5SigPass.name: ltmTcpProfileMd5SigPass
ltmTcpProfileMd5SigPass.description: This is a plaintext passphrase which may be between 1 and 80 characters in length, and is used in a shared-secret scheme to implement the spoof-prevention parts of RFC2385.

ltmTcpProfileAbc.name: ltmTcpProfileAbc
ltmTcpProfileAbc.description: The state that if it is true, count the number of bytes acked rather than the number of returning ACKs from the peer when in the linear congestion-window expansion phase of a TCP connection. This algorithm and its benefits are described in RFC3465 (Appropriate Byte Counting).

ltmTcpProfileCongestionCtrl.name: ltmTcpProfileCongestionCtrl
ltmTcpProfileCongestionCtrl.description: The TCP congestion control mode, guiding cwnd growth. reno - RENO congestion control mode; newreno - new RENO congestion control mode; scalable - scalable congestion control mode. It will do MIMD on cwnd besides NewReno retransmission; highspeed - high-speed congestion control mode, per RFC3649; none - no congestion control; vegas - vegas congestion control, delay-based; illinois - illinois congestion control, hybrid loss and delay; woodside - woodside congestion control, hybrid loss and delay; chd - chd congestion control, queue-delay based; cdg - cdg congestion control, RTT based; cubic - cubic congestion control, optimzed for high latency, high bandwidth connections; westwood - westwood+ congestion control, bandwidth estimation.

ltmTcpProfileDsack.name: ltmTcpProfileDsack
ltmTcpProfileDsack.description: The state that if true, enable support for RFC2883 D-SACK (Duplicate Selective Acknowledgement).

ltmTcpProfileCmetricsCache.name: ltmTcpProfileCmetricsCache
ltmTcpProfileCmetricsCache.description: The state that if true, use the routing table metrics cache to retrieve the last-known tcp congestion parameters. (Congestion window, round-trip-times, and slow-start threshold.)

ltmTcpProfileVerifiedAccept.name: ltmTcpProfileVerifiedAccept
ltmTcpProfileVerifiedAccept.description: The state that if true, the device must not respond to the clients SYN with a SYN-ACK until it receives a SYN-ACK from the server, indicating that the port is open.

ltmTcpProfilePktLossIgnoreRate.name: ltmTcpProfilePktLossIgnoreRate
ltmTcpProfilePktLossIgnoreRate.description: Specifies the threshold of packets lost per million at which the system should perform congestion control. Measured in packets per million. Valid values are from 0 to 1000000.

ltmTcpProfilePktLossIgnoreBurst.name: ltmTcpProfilePktLossIgnoreBurst
ltmTcpProfilePktLossIgnoreBurst.description: Specifies the likelihood of performing congestion control when multiple packets in a row are lost even if the loss threshold has not been exceeded. Valid values are from 0 to 32. Higher values decrease the likelihood of performing congestion control.

ltmTcpProfileZeroWindowTimeout.name: ltmTcpProfileZeroWindowTimeout
ltmTcpProfileZeroWindowTimeout.description: Specifies the timeout in milliseconds for terminating a connection with an effective zero length TCP transmit window. The timeout starts when the peer advertises a zero length TCP window or when enough data has been sent to fill the previously advertised window. The timer is canceled when a non-zero length window is received. The default is 20000 milliseconds.

ltmTcpProfileInitCwnd.name: ltmTcpProfileInitCwnd
ltmTcpProfileInitCwnd.description: Initial congestion window size for connections to this destination. Actual window size is this value multiplied by the MSS (Maximal Segment Size) for same connection. The default is zero, meaning to use the values specified in RFC2414. Allowed values are in the range of 0 to 16.

ltmTcpProfileInitRwnd.name: ltmTcpProfileInitRwnd
ltmTcpProfileInitRwnd.description: Initial receive window size for connections to this destination. The actual window size is this value multiplied by the MSS (Maximal Segment Size) of the connection. The default value is zero, meaning to use Slow Start value. Allowed values are in the range of 0 to 16.

ltmTcpProfileDelayWindowControl.name: ltmTcpProfileDelayWindowControl
ltmTcpProfileDelayWindowControl.description: If enabled, uses an estimate of queueing delay as a measure of congestion to control, in addition to the normal loss based control, the amount of data sent.

ltmTcpProfileSynRtoBase.name: ltmTcpProfileSynRtoBase
ltmTcpProfileSynRtoBase.description: Initial RTO (Retransmission TimeOut) base multiplier for SYN retransmission, specified in milliseconds. This value is modified by the exponential backoff table to select the interval for subsequent retransmissions.

ltmTcpProfileTimestamps.name: ltmTcpProfileTimestamps
ltmTcpProfileTimestamps.description: The state that if true, enables support for RFC1323 timestamps (high bandwidth TCP extension).

ltmTcpProfileMinRto.name: ltmTcpProfileMinRto
ltmTcpProfileMinRto.description: Specifies the minimum TCP retransmission timeout in milliseconds. The timeout starts when the sender sends a packet containing data. The timer is canceled when all outstanding data has been acknowledged. The timer restarts when an ACK is received to acknowledge new data. The default is 0 milliseconds; which means using the TCP stack default. Maximum value is 5000 milliseconds.

ltmTcpProfileMptcp.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcp
ltmTcpProfileMptcp.description: The state that, if true, enabled all incoming flows handle by the MPTCP stack allowing for support of multipath enabled connections.

ltmTcpProfileRatePace.name: ltmTcpProfileRatePace
ltmTcpProfileRatePace.description: The state that, when true, enables pacing of data transmission.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpCsum.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpCsum
ltmTcpProfileMptcpCsum.description: The state that, when true, enabled checksums support by this MPTCP enabled device.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpCsumVerify.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpCsumVerify
ltmTcpProfileMptcpCsumVerify.description: The state that, when true, enables verifing incoming checksums, and checksum failure causes connection abort.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpDebug.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpDebug
ltmTcpProfileMptcpDebug.description: The state that, when true, enables debug logging and statistics for MPTCP.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpFallback.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpFallback
ltmTcpProfileMptcpFallback.description: The MPTCP fallback control mode, reboot - reboot control mode; retransmit - retransmit control mode; activeaccept - activeaccept control mode; accept - accept control mode.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpJoinmax.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpJoinmax
ltmTcpProfileMptcpJoinmax.description: Specifies the maximum number of simultaneous join attempts on a given flow. Default value is 5. Maximum value is 20.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpNojoindssack.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpNojoindssack
ltmTcpProfileMptcpNojoindssack.description: The state that, when true, the no DSS option is sent on the JOIN ACK.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpRtomax.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpRtomax
ltmTcpProfileMptcpRtomax.description: Specifies the the number of RTOs before declaring subflow dead. Default value is 5. Maximum value is 12. Minimum value is 3.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpRxmitmin.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpRxmitmin
ltmTcpProfileMptcpRxmitmin.description: Specifies the minimum value (in milliseconds) of retransmission timer for these MPTCP flows. Default value is 1000. Maximum value is 5000. Minimum value is 200.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpSubflowmax.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpSubflowmax
ltmTcpProfileMptcpSubflowmax.description: Specifies the maximum number of MPTCP subflows for a single flow. Default value is 6. Maximum value is 10.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpMakeafterbreak.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpMakeafterbreak
ltmTcpProfileMptcpMakeafterbreak.description: The state that, when true, causes after break functionality allowing for Long-Lived MPTCP sessions.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpTimeout.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpTimeout
ltmTcpProfileMptcpTimeout.description: Specifies the timeout value to discard long-lived sessions that do not have an active flow. Default value is 3600 sec. Maximum value is 36000 sec.

ltmTcpProfileMptcpFastjoin.name: ltmTcpProfileMptcpFastjoin
ltmTcpProfileMptcpFastjoin.description: The state that, when true, enables FAST join, allowing data to be sent on the MP_JOIN SYN, which can allow a server response to occur in parallel with the JOIN

ltmTcpProfileEarlyRetransmit.name: ltmTcpProfileEarlyRetransmit
ltmTcpProfileEarlyRetransmit.description: The state that if true, enables support for RFC5827 Early Retransmit

ltmTcpProfileTailLossProbe.name: ltmTcpProfileTailLossProbe
ltmTcpProfileTailLossProbe.description: The state that if true, enables support for Tail Loss Probe

ltmTcpProfileStatResetStats.name: ltmTcpProfileStatResetStats
ltmTcpProfileStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmTcpProfileStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmTcpProfileStatNumber.name: ltmTcpProfileStatNumber
ltmTcpProfileStatNumber.description: The number of ltmTcpProfileStat entries in the table.

ltmTcpProfileStatTable.name: ltmTcpProfileStatTable
ltmTcpProfileStatTable.description: A table containing statistic information of TCP profile.

ltmTcpProfileStatName.name: ltmTcpProfileStatName
ltmTcpProfileStatName.description: The name of a TCP profile.

ltmTcpProfileStatOpen.name: ltmTcpProfileStatOpen
ltmTcpProfileStatOpen.description: The number of current open connections.

ltmTcpProfileStatCloseWait.name: ltmTcpProfileStatCloseWait
ltmTcpProfileStatCloseWait.description: The number of current connections in CLOSE-WAIT/LAST-ACK.

ltmTcpProfileStatFinWait.name: ltmTcpProfileStatFinWait
ltmTcpProfileStatFinWait.description: The number of current connections in FIN-WAIT/CLOSING.

ltmTcpProfileStatTimeWait.name: ltmTcpProfileStatTimeWait
ltmTcpProfileStatTimeWait.description: The number of current connections in TIME-WAIT.

ltmTcpProfileStatAcceptfails.name: ltmTcpProfileStatAcceptfails
ltmTcpProfileStatAcceptfails.description: The number of connections not accepted.

ltmTcpProfileStatExpires.name: ltmTcpProfileStatExpires
ltmTcpProfileStatExpires.description: The number of connections expired due to idle timeout.

ltmTcpProfileStatAbandons.name: ltmTcpProfileStatAbandons
ltmTcpProfileStatAbandons.description: The number of connections abandoned connections due to retries/keep-alives.

ltmTcpProfileStatRxooseg.name: ltmTcpProfileStatRxooseg
ltmTcpProfileStatRxooseg.description: The number of out of order segments.

ltmUdpProfileNumber.name: ltmUdpProfileNumber
ltmUdpProfileNumber.description: The number of ltmUdpProfile entries in the table.

ltmUdpProfileTable.name: ltmUdpProfileTable
ltmUdpProfileTable.description: A table containing information of UDP profile.

ltmUdpProfileName.name: ltmUdpProfileName
ltmUdpProfileName.description: The name of a UDP profile.

ltmUdpProfileConfigSource.name: ltmUdpProfileConfigSource
ltmUdpProfileConfigSource.description: The state that specifies whether this is a base/pre-configured profile or user defined profile.

ltmUdpProfileDefaultName.name: ltmUdpProfileDefaultName
ltmUdpProfileDefaultName.description: The name of the profile from which the specified profile derives its attribute default values.

ltmUdpProfileIdleTimeout.name: ltmUdpProfileIdleTimeout
ltmUdpProfileIdleTimeout.description: The umber of seconds without traffic before a flow is eligible for deletion.

ltmUdpProfileIpTosToClient.name: ltmUdpProfileIpTosToClient
ltmUdpProfileIpTosToClient.description: The IP type of service set in packets sent to client. Default:None.

ltmUdpProfileLinkQosToClient.name: ltmUdpProfileLinkQosToClient
ltmUdpProfileLinkQosToClient.description: The link quality of service set in packets sent to client. Default:None.

ltmUdpProfileDatagramLb.name: ltmUdpProfileDatagramLb
ltmUdpProfileDatagramLb.description: The state indicating whether or not to load balance each UDP datagram separately.

ltmUdpProfileAllowNoPayload.name: ltmUdpProfileAllowNoPayload
ltmUdpProfileAllowNoPayload.description: The state indicating whether to not allow the passage of datagrams with no payload.

ltmUdpProfileStatResetStats.name: ltmUdpProfileStatResetStats
ltmUdpProfileStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmUdpProfileStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmUdpProfileStatNumber.name: ltmUdpProfileStatNumber
ltmUdpProfileStatNumber.description: The number of ltmUdpProfileStat entries in the table.

ltmUdpProfileStatTable.name: ltmUdpProfileStatTable
ltmUdpProfileStatTable.description: A table containing information of UDP profile.

ltmUdpProfileStatName.name: ltmUdpProfileStatName
ltmUdpProfileStatName.description: The name of a UDP profile.

ltmUdpProfileStatOpen.name: ltmUdpProfileStatOpen
ltmUdpProfileStatOpen.description: The number of current open connections.

ltmUdpProfileStatAcceptfails.name: ltmUdpProfileStatAcceptfails
ltmUdpProfileStatAcceptfails.description: The number of connections not accepted.

ltmUdpProfileStatExpires.name: ltmUdpProfileStatExpires
ltmUdpProfileStatExpires.description: The number of connections expired due to idle timeout.

ltmUdpProfileStatRxunreach.name: ltmUdpProfileStatRxunreach
ltmUdpProfileStatRxunreach.description: The number of received ICMP un-reached.

ltmRuleNumber.name: ltmRuleNumber
ltmRuleNumber.description: The number of ltmRule entries in the table.

ltmRuleTable.name: ltmRuleTable
ltmRuleTable.description: A table containing information of rules.

ltmRuleDefinition.name: ltmRuleDefinition
ltmRuleDefinition.description: Deprecated! The definition of the specified rule.

ltmRuleConfigSource.name: ltmRuleConfigSource
ltmRuleConfigSource.description: The type of rule that the specified rule is associating with. It is either a base/pre-configured rule or user defined rule.

ltmRuleEventNumber.name: ltmRuleEventNumber
ltmRuleEventNumber.description: The number of ltmRuleEvent entries in the table.

ltmRuleEventTable.name: ltmRuleEventTable
ltmRuleEventTable.description: A table containing information of rule events.

ltmRuleEventEventType.name: ltmRuleEventEventType
ltmRuleEventEventType.description: The event type which the rule is used for.

ltmRuleEventPriority.name: ltmRuleEventPriority
ltmRuleEventPriority.description: The execution priority of this rule event.

ltmRuleEventScript.name: ltmRuleEventScript
ltmRuleEventScript.description: Deprecated!. The TCL script for this rule event.

ltmRuleEventStatResetStats.name: ltmRuleEventStatResetStats
ltmRuleEventStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmRuleEventStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmRuleEventStatNumber.name: ltmRuleEventStatNumber
ltmRuleEventStatNumber.description: The number of ltmRuleEventStat entries in the table.

ltmRuleEventStatTable.name: ltmRuleEventStatTable
ltmRuleEventStatTable.description: A table containing statistic information of rules.

ltmRuleEventStatEventType.name: ltmRuleEventStatEventType
ltmRuleEventStatEventType.description: The type of the event associated with the specified rule.

ltmRuleEventStatFailures.name: ltmRuleEventStatFailures
ltmRuleEventStatFailures.description: The number of failures for executing the specified rule.

ltmRuleEventStatAborts.name: ltmRuleEventStatAborts
ltmRuleEventStatAborts.description: The number of aborts when executing the specified rule.

ltmRuleEventStatTotalExecutions.name: ltmRuleEventStatTotalExecutions
ltmRuleEventStatTotalExecutions.description: The total number of event executions for the specified rule.

ltmRuleEventStatAvgCycles.name: ltmRuleEventStatAvgCycles
ltmRuleEventStatAvgCycles.description: The average of cycles spent during an execution of the specified rule event.

ltmRuleEventStatMaxCycles.name: ltmRuleEventStatMaxCycles
ltmRuleEventStatMaxCycles.description: The maximum of cycles spent during an execution of the specified rule event.

ltmRuleEventStatMinCycles.name: ltmRuleEventStatMinCycles
ltmRuleEventStatMinCycles.description: The minimum of cycles spent during an execution of the specified rule event.

ltmSnatNumber.name: ltmSnatNumber
ltmSnatNumber.description: The number of ltmSnat entries in the table.

ltmSnatTable.name: ltmSnatTable
ltmSnatTable.description: A table containing information of SNAT.

ltmSnatName.name: ltmSnatName
ltmSnatName.description: The name of a SNAT. It is a named object in the definition of a standard or a selective SNAT. Standard SNATs translate to a single address, while selective SNATs translate to a pool of translation addresses.

ltmSnatSfFlags.name: ltmSnatSfFlags
ltmSnatSfFlags.description: The state indicating whether connection mirroring is enabled or not for the specified SNAT.

ltmSnatType.name: ltmSnatType
ltmSnatType.description: The translation type of the specified SNAT. none - No SNAT (invalid default); transaddr - The SNAT uses a single translation address; snatpool - The SNAT uses a SNAT pool of translation addresses; automap - The SNAT uses self IP addresses.

ltmSnatTransAddrType.name: ltmSnatTransAddrType
ltmSnatTransAddrType.description: The IP address type of ltmSnatTransAddr

ltmSnatTransAddr.name: ltmSnatTransAddr
ltmSnatTransAddr.description: The translation address used by the specified SNAT if the SNAT translates to a translation address. It is interpreted within the context of a ltmSnatTransAddrType value.

ltmSnatSnatpoolName.name: ltmSnatSnatpoolName
ltmSnatSnatpoolName.description: The name of a SNAT pool, which is a pool of SNAT translation addresses. It is used by the specified SNAT if the SNAT translates to a pool.

ltmSnatListedEnabledVlans.name: ltmSnatListedEnabledVlans
ltmSnatListedEnabledVlans.description: The state indicating whether associated VLANs are SNAT enabled or not. The associated VLANs are listed in ltmSnatVlanTable.

ltmSnatStatResetStats.name: ltmSnatStatResetStats
ltmSnatStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmSnatStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmSnatStatNumber.name: ltmSnatStatNumber
ltmSnatStatNumber.description: The number of ltmSnatStat entries in the table.

ltmSnatStatTable.name: ltmSnatStatTable
ltmSnatStatTable.description: A table containing statistic information of SNAT.

ltmSnatStatClientPktsIn.name: ltmSnatStatClientPktsIn
ltmSnatStatClientPktsIn.description: The number of packets received from client-side.

ltmSnatStatClientBytesIn.name: ltmSnatStatClientBytesIn
ltmSnatStatClientBytesIn.description: The number of bytes received from client-side.

ltmSnatStatClientPktsOut.name: ltmSnatStatClientPktsOut
ltmSnatStatClientPktsOut.description: The number of packets sent to client-side.

ltmSnatStatClientBytesOut.name: ltmSnatStatClientBytesOut
ltmSnatStatClientBytesOut.description: The number of bytes sent to client-side.

ltmSnatVlanVlanName.name: ltmSnatVlanVlanName
ltmSnatVlanVlanName.description: The name of a VLAN associated with the specified SNAT. Only when ltmSnatListedEnabledVlans is set to enable, SNAT is enabled on the VLAN.

ltmTransAddrUnitId.name: ltmTransAddrUnitId

ltmVirtualServSfFlags.name: ltmVirtualServSfFlags

ltmVirtualServTranslateAddr.name: ltmVirtualServTranslateAddr

ltmVirtualServTranslatePort.name: ltmVirtualServTranslatePort
ltmVirtualServTranslatePort.description: The state indicating whether the port of the specified virtual server should be translated.

ltmVirtualServType.name: ltmVirtualServType
ltmVirtualServType.description: The type supported by the specified virtual server. poolbased - The virtual server is based on a pool; ipforward - The virtual server only supports IP forwarding. There is no load balancing on this type of virtual server; l2forward - The virtual server only supports L2 forwarding. There is no load balancing on this type of virtual server; reject - All connections going to this virtual server will be rejected, and resets will be sent; fastl4 - The virtual server is associated with a Fast L4 profile; fasthttp - The virtual server is associated with a Fast HTTP profile; stateless - The virtual server accepts traffic matching the virtual server address and load balances the packet to the pool members without attempting to match the packet to a pre-existing connection on the connection table; dhcp-relay - The virtual server relays DHCP client requests for an IP address to one or more DHCP servers and provides DHCP server responses with an available IP address for the client; internal - The virtual server supports modification of HTTP requests and responses.

ltmVirtualServSnatType.name: ltmVirtualServSnatType
ltmVirtualServSnatType.description: Deprecated! Replaced by Source Address Translation type associated with the specified virtual server. The type of SNAT associated with the specified virtual server. none - No SNAT used by the virtual server; transaddr - The SNAT uses a single translation address (invalid type); snatpool - The SNAT uses a SNAT pool of translation addresses; automap - The SNAT uses self IP addresses.

ltmVirtualAddrRouteAdvertisement.name: ltmVirtualAddrRouteAdvertisement

ltmVirtualAddrAvailabilityState.name: ltmVirtualAddrAvailabilityState
ltmVirtualAddrAvailabilityState.description: Deprecated! Replaced by ltmVsAddrStatusAvailState under ltmVirtualAddrStatus. The state of the specified virtual address availability indicated in color.

ltmVirtualAddrEnabledState.name: ltmVirtualAddrEnabledState
ltmVirtualAddrEnabledState.description: Deprecated! Replaced by ltmVsAddrStatusEnabledState under ltmVirtualAddrStatus. The state of the specified virtual address activity status, as specified by the user.

ltmVirtualAddrServer.name: ltmVirtualAddrServer
ltmVirtualAddrServer.description: That state to control how status of virtual address is depending on status of virtual server. none: virtual address is always green regardless of virtual server status. any: any virtual server is green, virtual address is green. all: all virtual servers must be green before virtual address is declared as green.

ltmVirtualAddrIsFloat.name: ltmVirtualAddrIsFloat
ltmVirtualAddrIsFloat.description: The state indicating whether the virtual address should be shared between the redundant pair. This is typically used in one-armed Combo pair, where GTM is only licensed on one of the boxes.

ltmVirtualAddrStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmVirtualAddrStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmVirtualAddrStatPvaTotConns.name: ltmVirtualAddrStatPvaTotConns

ltmVirtualAddrStatPvaCurConns.name: ltmVirtualAddrStatPvaCurConns
ltmVirtualAddrStatPvaCurConns.description: The current hardware accelerated connections to the specified virtual address.

ltmVirtualAddrStatTotPvaAssistConn.name: ltmVirtualAddrStatTotPvaAssistConn
ltmVirtualAddrStatTotPvaAssistConn.description: The total number of connections to the specified virtual address, which are partially hardware accelerated.

ltmVirtualAddrStatCurrPvaAssistConn.name: ltmVirtualAddrStatCurrPvaAssistConn
ltmVirtualAddrStatCurrPvaAssistConn.description: The current number of connections to the specified virtual address, which are partially hardware accelerated.

ltmFastHttpProfileNumber.name: ltmFastHttpProfileNumber
ltmFastHttpProfileNumber.description: The number of ltmFastHttpProfile entries in the table.

ltmFastHttpProfileTable.name: ltmFastHttpProfileTable
ltmFastHttpProfileTable.description: A table containing information of Fast HTTP profile.

ltmFastHttpProfileName.name: ltmFastHttpProfileName
ltmFastHttpProfileName.description: The name of a fast HTTP profile.

ltmFastHttpProfileConfigSource.name: ltmFastHttpProfileConfigSource
ltmFastHttpProfileConfigSource.description: The state that specifies whether this is a base/pre-configured profile or user defined profile.

ltmFastHttpProfileDefaultName.name: ltmFastHttpProfileDefaultName
ltmFastHttpProfileDefaultName.description: The name of the profile from which the specified profile derives its attribute default values.

ltmFastHttpProfileResetOnTimeout.name: ltmFastHttpProfileResetOnTimeout
ltmFastHttpProfileResetOnTimeout.description: If true and a TCP connection exceeds its idle_timeout, send a reset in addition to deleting the connection.

ltmFastHttpProfileIdleTimeout.name: ltmFastHttpProfileIdleTimeout
ltmFastHttpProfileIdleTimeout.description: Number of seconds without traffic before a connection is eligible for deletion.

ltmFastHttpProfileMssOverride.name: ltmFastHttpProfileMssOverride
ltmFastHttpProfileMssOverride.description: If non-zero and less than the 1460 default, this value overrides the maximum segment size for server-side flows.

ltmFastHttpProfileClientCloseTimeout.name: ltmFastHttpProfileClientCloseTimeout
ltmFastHttpProfileClientCloseTimeout.description: Idle timeout override when waiting for the client to close. This occurs after a client FIN is received or after a FIN is sent. 0 is immediate, -1 is indefinite.

ltmFastHttpProfileServerCloseTimeout.name: ltmFastHttpProfileServerCloseTimeout
ltmFastHttpProfileServerCloseTimeout.description: Idle timeout override when waiting for the server to close. This occurs if the server flow is not suitable for reuse or after a FIN is received on an unspliced server connection. 0 is immediate, -1 is indefinite.

ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMaxSize.name: ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMaxSize
ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMaxSize.description: Maximum number of connections to any given LB pool. 0 for unlimited.

ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMinSize.name: ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMinSize
ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMinSize.description: Minimum number of connections to any given LB pool. 0 is an acceptable value.

ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolStep.name: ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolStep
ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolStep.description: Connection ramp-up increment. Must be greater than 0.

ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMaxReuse.name: ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMaxReuse
ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolMaxReuse.description: Maximum number of times a server-side flow will be reused. 0 for unlimited.

ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolIdleTimeout.name: ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolIdleTimeout
ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolIdleTimeout.description: Idle timeout override for unspliced server-side flows in the reuse pool. 0 is disabled, i.e. use the default idle timeout.

ltmFastHttpProfileMaxHeaderSize.name: ltmFastHttpProfileMaxHeaderSize
ltmFastHttpProfileMaxHeaderSize.description: Maximum amount of data that will be buffered in order to make a content-switching decision.

ltmFastHttpProfileMaxRequests.name: ltmFastHttpProfileMaxRequests
ltmFastHttpProfileMaxRequests.description: Maximum number of requests on a client-side flow before the flow is shutdown. 0 for unlimited.

ltmFastHttpProfileInsertXforwardedFor.name: ltmFastHttpProfileInsertXforwardedFor
ltmFastHttpProfileInsertXforwardedFor.description: The state whether to insert or replace X-Forwarded-For header with client IP.

ltmFastHttpProfileHttp11CloseWorkarounds.name: ltmFastHttpProfileHttp11CloseWorkarounds
ltmFastHttpProfileHttp11CloseWorkarounds.description: The state to workaround problems with certain brands of benchmarking software that cannot handle FIN-PUSH on HTTP/1.1 responses.

ltmFastHttpProfileHeaderInsert.name: ltmFastHttpProfileHeaderInsert
ltmFastHttpProfileHeaderInsert.description: Insert the given string as a header. If the header already exists, it is not replaced. Unlike HTTP, this string does not support rule command expansion.

ltmFastHttpProfileUncleanShutdown.name: ltmFastHttpProfileUncleanShutdown
ltmFastHttpProfileUncleanShutdown.description: The mode to indicate whether to do unclean shutdown for client connections.

ltmFastHttpProfileForceHttp10Response.name: ltmFastHttpProfileForceHttp10Response
ltmFastHttpProfileForceHttp10Response.description: The state to indicate whether to rewrite server's HTTP version to 1.0 in status line in order to dissuade the client from pipelining or chunking.

ltmFastHttpProfileLayer7.name: ltmFastHttpProfileLayer7
ltmFastHttpProfileLayer7.description: The state that if false, we don't parse HTTP requests. This is useful for providing SYN-proxy protection for L4 connections through a SNAT where the client sends data to the server before the server responds.

ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolReplenish.name: ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolReplenish
ltmFastHttpProfileConnpoolReplenish.description: The state that specifies whether the connpool should be replenished to its prior number of connections when a connection is closed by the server. If this is disabled, then we will only replenish a closed server side connection residing in the connpool if there are less than ltmFastHttpProfileMinSize (see above) connections in the pool.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatResetStats.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatResetStats
ltmFastHttpProfileStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmFastHttpProfileStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatNumber.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatNumber
ltmFastHttpProfileStatNumber.description: The number of ltmFastHttpProfileStat entries in the table.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatTable.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatTable
ltmFastHttpProfileStatTable.description: A table containing statistic information of Fast HTTP profile.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatName.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatName
ltmFastHttpProfileStatName.description: The name of a fast HTTP profile.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientSyns.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientSyns
ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientSyns.description: The total number of client SYN cookies generated.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientAccepts.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientAccepts
ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientAccepts.description: The total number of client TCP accepts.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatServerConnects.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatServerConnects
ltmFastHttpProfileStatServerConnects.description: The total number of server TCP connects.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolCurSize.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolCurSize
ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolCurSize.description: Number of available server-side flows in the reuse pool.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolMaxSize.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolMaxSize
ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolMaxSize.description: Max number of available server-side flows in the reuse pool.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolReuses.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolReuses
ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolReuses.description: Number of times a server-side flow was reused from the pool.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolExhausted.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolExhausted
ltmFastHttpProfileStatConnpoolExhausted.description: Number of times the reuse pool was exhausted.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatNumberReqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatNumberReqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatNumberReqs.description: The total number of http requests.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatUnbufferedReqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatUnbufferedReqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatUnbufferedReqs.description: The total number of unbuffered requests.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatGetReqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatGetReqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatGetReqs.description: The total number of get requests.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatPostReqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatPostReqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatPostReqs.description: The total number of post requests.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatV9Reqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatV9Reqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatV9Reqs.description: The total number of version 9 requests.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatV10Reqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatV10Reqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatV10Reqs.description: The total number of version 10 requests.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatV11Reqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatV11Reqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatV11Reqs.description: The total number of version 11 requests.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp2xxCnt.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp2xxCnt
ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp2xxCnt.description: Number of server-side responses in range of 200 to 206 (successful responses).

ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp3xxCnt.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp3xxCnt
ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp3xxCnt.description: Number of server-side responses in range of 300 to 307 (redirection responses).

ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp4xxCnt.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp4xxCnt
ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp4xxCnt.description: Number of server-side responses in range of 400 to 417 (client errors).

ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp5xxCnt.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp5xxCnt
ltmFastHttpProfileStatResp5xxCnt.description: Number of server-side responses in range of 500 to 505 (server errors).

ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientRxBad.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientRxBad
ltmFastHttpProfileStatClientRxBad.description: Number of bad TCP segments dropped from client-side.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatServerRxBad.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatServerRxBad
ltmFastHttpProfileStatServerRxBad.description: Number of bad TCP segments dropped from server-side.

ltmFastHttpProfileStatPipelinedReqs.name: ltmFastHttpProfileStatPipelinedReqs
ltmFastHttpProfileStatPipelinedReqs.description: Number of pipelined HTTP requests detected.

ltmXmlProfileAbortOnError.description: Deprecated! The state that if true, abort the connection on errors.

ltmXmlProfileMaxBufferSize.description: Deprecated! The value that specifies the maximum buffer size for the specified profile.

ltmXmlProfileMultipleQueryMatches.description: The state that if true, multiple matches for a single XPath query are enabled.

ltmXmlProfileStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmXmlProfileStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumber.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumber
ltmXmlProfileStatNumber.description: The number of ltmXmlProfileStat entries in the table.

ltmXmlProfileStatTable.description: A table containing statistic information of XML profile.

ltmXmlProfileStatName.name: ltmXmlProfileStatName
ltmXmlProfileStatName.description: The name of a XML profile.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumErrors.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumErrors
ltmXmlProfileStatNumErrors.description: Deprecated! The total number of XML parsing errors.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumInspectedDocuments.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumInspectedDocuments
ltmXmlProfileStatNumInspectedDocuments.description: The total number of inspected XML documents.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithOneMatc.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithOneMatch
ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithOneMatc.description: The total number of XML documents in which one XPath query match was found.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithTwoMatc.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithTwoMatches
ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithTwoMatc.description: The total number of XML documents in which two XPath query matches were found.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithThreeMa.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithThreeMatches
ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithThreeMa.description: The total number of XML documents in which three XPath query matches were found.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithNoMatch.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithNoMatches
ltmXmlProfileStatNumDocumentsWithNoMatch.description: The total number of XML documents in which no XPath query matches were found.

ltmXmlProfileStatNumMalformedDocuments.name: ltmXmlProfileStatNumMalformedDocuments
ltmXmlProfileStatNumMalformedDocuments.description: The total number of malformed XML documents.

ltmRamUriExclNumber.description: Deprecated!. The number of ltmHttpProfileRamUriExcl entries in the table.

ltmRamUriInclNumber.description: Deprecated!. The number of ltmHttpProfileRamUriIncl entries in the table.

ltmRamUriInclTable.description: A table containing information of RAM cached includes URI's in HTTP profiles.

ltmRamUriInclName.description: The name of a HTTP profile.

ltmRamUriPinNumber.name: ltmRamUriPinNumber
ltmRamUriPinNumber.description: Deprecated!. The number of ltmHttpProfileRamUriPin entries in the table.

ltmRamUriPinTable.description: A table containing information of RAM cached URI's pinned in HTTP profiles.

ltmDnsProfileNumber.name: ltmDnsProfileNumber
ltmDnsProfileNumber.description: The number of ltmDnsProfile entries in the table.

ltmDnsProfileTable.name: ltmDnsProfileTable
ltmDnsProfileTable.description: A table containing information for DNS profiles.

ltmDnsProfileName.name: ltmDnsProfileName
ltmDnsProfileName.description: The name of a DNS profile.

ltmDnsProfileConfigSource.name: ltmDnsProfileConfigSource
ltmDnsProfileConfigSource.description: The state that specifies whether this is a base/pre-configured profile or user defined profile.

ltmDnsProfileDefaultName.name: ltmDnsProfileDefaultName
ltmDnsProfileDefaultName.description: The name of the profile from which the specified profile derives its attribute default values.

ltmDnsProfileGtmEnabled.name: ltmDnsProfileGtmEnabled
ltmDnsProfileGtmEnabled.description: The state indicating whether or not to allow GTMD (Global Traffic Management Daemon) to handle DNS resolution for DNS queries and responses that contain Wide IP names.

ltmDnsProfileDns64Mode.name: ltmDnsProfileDns64Mode
ltmDnsProfileDns64Mode.description: The mode which specifies whether to perform DNS64 translation, and how to perform it. disable - no DNS64 translation is performed; secondary - send AAAA first, if no result send another A; immediate - send both AAAA and A together; v4only - send only A request.

ltmDnsProfileDns64PrefixType.name: ltmDnsProfileDns64PrefixType
ltmDnsProfileDns64PrefixType.description: The IP address type of DNS64 prefix.

ltmDnsProfileDns64Prefix.name: ltmDnsProfileDns64Prefix
ltmDnsProfileDns64Prefix.description: The prefix for DNS64 mapping for the specified DNS profile.

ltmDnsProfileDns64AdditionalRewrite.name: ltmDnsProfileDns64AdditionalRewrite
ltmDnsProfileDns64AdditionalRewrite.description: Controls system behavior when a DNS response contains AAAA or A record(s) in the additional section. When DNS64 is enabled, this option selects how to rewrite (or not rewrite) these entries. disable - do not rewrite records in the additional section; v6only - the system deletes any A records in the additional section; v4only - the system deletes any AAAA records in the additional section, and rewrites A records into AAAA by prepending the IPv6 prefix; any - the system allows any AAAA records in the additional section, and rewrites A records into AAAA by prepending the IPv6 prefix.

ltmDnsProfileDnsLastAction.name: ltmDnsProfileDnsLastAction
ltmDnsProfileDnsLastAction.description: Last action that will be taken if there is no matching zone name, i.e. a DNS query does not match a GTM Wide IP name, is not a DNSSEC query type (e.g. DNSKEY, etc.), does not match a DNS-Express Zone name, and DNS cache is not configured/enabled. allow - last action is to pass the DNS query to either a pool member or on-box BIND. This is pre-11.x behavior; drop - last action is to drop the DNS query; reject - last action is to send a DNS response with a REFUSED rcode set in the header; hint - last action is to send a DNS response with a list of root name servers; noerror - last action is to send a DNS response with a NOERROR rcode set in the header.

ltmDnsProfileUseLocalBind.name: ltmDnsProfileUseLocalBind
ltmDnsProfileUseLocalBind.description: The state indicating whether or not local BIND is used as a DNS resource.

ltmDnsProfileDnsExpressEnabled.name: ltmDnsProfileDnsExpressEnabled
ltmDnsProfileDnsExpressEnabled.description: The state indicating whether or not DNS Express is enabled for the specified profile.

ltmDnsProfileDnssecEnabled.name: ltmDnsProfileDnssecEnabled
ltmDnsProfileDnssecEnabled.description: The state indicating whether or not DNSSEC is enabled for the specified profile.

ltmDnsProfileCacheEnabled.name: ltmDnsProfileCacheEnabled
ltmDnsProfileCacheEnabled.description: The state indicating whether or not DNS cache is enabled for the specified profile.

ltmDnsProfileDnsCache.name: ltmDnsProfileDnsCache

ltmDnsProfileProcessRd.name: ltmDnsProfileProcessRd

ltmHttpCompressionProfileNumber.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileNumber
ltmHttpCompressionProfileNumber.description: The number of ltmHttpCompressionProfile entries in the table.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileTable.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileTable
ltmHttpCompressionProfileTable.description: A table containing information of HTTP Compression profiles.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileName.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileName
ltmHttpCompressionProfileName.description: The name of a HTTP compression profile.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileConfigSource.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileConfigSource
ltmHttpCompressionProfileConfigSource.description: The state that specifies whether this is a base/pre-configured profile or user defined profile.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileDefaultName.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileDefaultName
ltmHttpCompressionProfileDefaultName.description: The name of the profile from which the specified profile derives its attribute default values.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileSelective.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileSelective
ltmHttpCompressionProfileSelective.description: The state that specifies whether selective compression is enabled.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileMinSize.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileMinSize
ltmHttpCompressionProfileMinSize.description: The value that specifies the minimum length of the server responses (in bytes) to be considered acceptable for compression.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileBufferSize.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileBufferSize
ltmHttpCompressionProfileBufferSize.description: The value that specifies the maximum number of uncompressed bytes that the compression proxy will buffer before it decides whether or not to compress the server's response, in case the server's response headers don't specify the content length of the response.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileVaryHeader.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileVaryHeader
ltmHttpCompressionProfileVaryHeader.description: The state that specifies whether to insert the header 'Vary: Accept-Encoding' in the server response for responses that have been compressed. If the 'Vary:' header already exists in the server response, then the value 'Accept-Encoding' will be appended to it.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileAllowHttp10.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileAllowHttp10
ltmHttpCompressionProfileAllowHttp10.description: The state that specifies whether to allow compression on responses to HTTP 1.0 requests.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipMemlevel.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipMemlevel
ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipMemlevel.description: The amount of memory that the proxy will use when doing compression. It must be an integer no less than 1 and no greater than 9. Higher values produce faster compression at the expense of more memory usage. The default memory level will be 8.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipWindowsize.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipWindowsize
ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipWindowsize.description: The number of bits in the window size that the compression proxy will use when compressing the server response. It should be an integer no less than 8 and no greater than 15. Higher values produce better compression ratios at the expense of more memory usage. The default window size will be 15.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipLevel.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipLevel
ltmHttpCompressionProfileGzipLevel.description: The speed of compression that is applied to the response. Minimum value is 1, maximum is 9. The lower numbers give faster compression with lower ratios, and higher numbers give slower compression with higher ratios.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileKeepAcceptEncod.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileKeepAcceptEncoding
ltmHttpCompressionProfileKeepAcceptEncod.description: The state of the option to keep client-encoding header.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileBrowserWorkarou.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileBrowserWorkarounds
ltmHttpCompressionProfileBrowserWorkarou.description: The option to control whether or not to disable compression for known browsers that cannot handle certain types of compressed responses properly. If it's true, compression for known browsers will be disabled.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaver.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaver
ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaver.description: The state indicating whether CPU saving mode is enable or not when doing compression.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaverHigh.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaverHigh
ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaverHigh.description: The CPU saver high threshold. When CPU utilization exceeds this value, compression is switched to NULL compression.

ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaverLow.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaverLow
ltmHttpCompressionProfileCpusaverLow.description: The CPU saver low threshold. When CPU utilization drops below this value, compression is switched to full throttle.

ltmHttpCompressionProfilePreferredMethod.name: ltmHttpCompressionProfilePreferredMethod
ltmHttpCompressionProfilePreferredMethod.description: The option for preferred compression method.

ltmHttpcompUriInclNumber.name: ltmHttpcompUriInclNumber
ltmHttpcompUriInclNumber.description: The number of ltmHttpCompressionProfileUriIncl entries in the table.

ltmHttpcompUriInclTable.name: ltmHttpcompUriInclTable
ltmHttpcompUriInclTable.description: A table containing information of regular expressions used to match the request URI part of the client requests during compression. A match must be found in at least one of the 'include' fields.

ltmHttpcompUriInclName.name: ltmHttpcompUriInclName
ltmHttpcompUriInclName.description: The name of a HTTP Compression profile.

ltmHttpcompUriInclIndex.name: ltmHttpcompUriInclIndex
ltmHttpcompUriInclIndex.description: The index of the regular expression used to match the request URI part of the client requests during compression in 'include' fields for the specified HTTP Compression profile.

ltmHttpcompUriInclUri.name: ltmHttpcompUriInclUri
ltmHttpcompUriInclUri.description: The regular expression used to match the request URI part of the client requests during compression in 'include' fields for the specified HTTP Compression profile.

ltmHttpcompUriExclNumber.name: ltmHttpcompUriExclNumber
ltmHttpcompUriExclNumber.description: The number of ltmHttpCompressionProfileUriExcl entries in the table.

ltmHttpcompUriExclTable.name: ltmHttpcompUriExclTable
ltmHttpcompUriExclTable.description: A table containing information of regular expressions used to match the request URI part of the client requests during compression. A match must be found in at least one of the 'exclude' fields.

ltmHttpcompUriExclName.name: ltmHttpcompUriExclName

ltmDnsCacheTable.description: A table containing information of DNS cache.

ltmDnsCacheType.name: ltmDnsCacheType
ltmDnsCacheType.description: The type of DNS cache. resolver - configures a DNS cache with a resolver on the BIG-IP system; validating-resolver - configures a DNS cache with a resolver and validator on the BIG-IP system; transparent-resolver - configures a DNS cache without a resolver on the BIG-IP system.

ltmDnsCacheMsgCacheSize.name: ltmDnsCacheMsgCacheSize
ltmDnsCacheMsgCacheSize.description: The number of bytes allocated to the message cache. The default value is 1m. Relevant to resolver, validating-resolver, and transparent-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheRrsetCacheSize.name: ltmDnsCacheRrsetCacheSize
ltmDnsCacheRrsetCacheSize.description: The number of bytes allocated to the resource records set cache. The default value is 10m. Relevant to resolver, validating-resolver, and transparent-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheAnswerDefaultZones.name: ltmDnsCacheAnswerDefaultZones
ltmDnsCacheAnswerDefaultZones.description: The state indicating whether or not the resolver answers queries for default zones: localhost, reverse 127.0.0.1 and ::1, and AS112 zones. The default value is no. Relevant to resolver, validating-resolver, and transparent-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheUseIpv4.name: ltmDnsCacheUseIpv4
ltmDnsCacheUseIpv4.description: The state indicating whether or not the resolver is enabled to send queries to IPv4 addresses. The default value is yes. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheUseIpv6.name: ltmDnsCacheUseIpv6
ltmDnsCacheUseIpv6.description: The state indicating whether or not the resolver is enabled to send queries to IPv6 addresses. The default value is yes. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheUseUdp.name: ltmDnsCacheUseUdp
ltmDnsCacheUseUdp.description: The state indicating whether or not the resolver is enabled to send queries over UDP. The default value is yes. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheUseTcp.name: ltmDnsCacheUseTcp
ltmDnsCacheUseTcp.description: The state indicating whether or not the resolver is enabled to send queries over TCP. The default value is yes. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheNameserverCacheCount.name: ltmDnsCacheNameserverCacheCount
ltmDnsCacheNameserverCacheCount.description: The number of DNS name-servers for which connection and capability data is cached. The default value is 16k. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentTcp.name: ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentTcp
ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentTcp.description: The maximum number of concurrent TCP flows used by the resolver. The default value is 20. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentUdp.name: ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentUdp
ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentUdp.description: The maximum number of concurrent UDP flows used by the resolver. The default value is 8192. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheUnwantedThreshold.name: ltmDnsCacheUnwantedThreshold
ltmDnsCacheUnwantedThreshold.description: The threshold count of unsolicited query replies which triggers an alert (potential DOS attack underway). The default value is zero (or off). Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheRouteDomainName.name: ltmDnsCacheRouteDomainName
ltmDnsCacheRouteDomainName.description: The name of the route domain used for resolver outbound traffic. The default value is the default route domain. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheIgnoreCd.name: ltmDnsCacheIgnoreCd
ltmDnsCacheIgnoreCd.description: The state indicating whether or not the validating-resolver ignores client queries setting of checking-disabled and performs validation anyway and only returns secure answers. The default value is no. Relevant to validating-resolver type.

ltmDnsCachePrefetchKey.name: ltmDnsCachePrefetchKey
ltmDnsCachePrefetchKey.description: The state indicating whether or not the validating-resolver fetches DNSKEY early in validation process. The default value is yes. Relevant to validating-resolver type.

ltmDnsCacheKeyCacheSize.name: ltmDnsCacheKeyCacheSize
ltmDnsCacheKeyCacheSize.description: The number of bytes allocated to the DNSKEY cache. The default value is 1m. Relevant to validating-resolver type.

ltmDnsCacheRandomizeQueryNameCase.name: ltmDnsCacheRandomizeQueryNameCase
ltmDnsCacheRandomizeQueryNameCase.description: The state indicating whether or not the resolver is enabled to randomize the case of query names. The default value is yes. Relevant to resolver and validating-resolver types.

ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentQueries.name: ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentQueries
ltmDnsCacheMaxConcurrentQueries.description: The maximum number of concurrent distinct queries used by the resolver. A query is identified by query name, type and class. If the number of distinct queries exceeds this limit, the resolver will try to find a query from the queue which arrives the earliest. Replace it with the new query if it has been in the queue longer than the allowed time. The default value is 1024.

ltmDnsCacheAllowedQueryTime.name: ltmDnsCacheAllowedQueryTime
ltmDnsCacheAllowedQueryTime.description: The time allowed for a query to stay in the queue before replaced by a new query when the number of concurrrent distinct queries exceeds the limit. The default value is 200 milliseconds.

ltmDnsSecurityStatTable.description: A table containing statistics information of DNS security.

ltmDnsSecurityStatFilteredDrops.description: The total number of dropped DNS packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatADrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatADrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatADrops.description: The total number of dropped A packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatAaaaDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatAaaaDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatAaaaDrops.description: The total number of dropped AAAA packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatAnyDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatAnyDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatAnyDrops.description: The total number of dropped ANY packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatCnameDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatCnameDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatCnameDrops.description: The total number of dropped CNAME packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatMxDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatMxDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatMxDrops.description: The total number of dropped MX packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatNsDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatNsDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatNsDrops.description: The total number of dropped NS packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatPtrDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatPtrDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatPtrDrops.description: The total number of dropped PTR packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatSoaDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatSoaDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatSoaDrops.description: The total number of dropped SOA packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatSrvDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatSrvDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatSrvDrops.description: The total number of dropped SRV packets due to filtering.

ltmDnsSecurityStatTxtDrops.name: ltmDnsSecurityStatTxtDrops
ltmDnsSecurityStatTxtDrops.description: The total number of dropped TXT packets due to filtering.

ltmBwcPolicyStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmBwcPolicyStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmBwcPolicyStatNumber.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatNumber
ltmBwcPolicyStatNumber.description: The number of ltmBwcPolicyStat entries in the table.

ltmBwcPolicyStatTable.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatTable
ltmBwcPolicyStatTable.description: A table containing statistics information of BWC policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatName.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatName
ltmBwcPolicyStatName.description: The name of BWC policy that is configured. There are many types of BWC policies. This name is string upto max of string name of policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPerSec.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPerSec
ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPerSec.description: The average input bytes/sec over last 4 seconds. These are bytes as processed by this policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPerSecOut.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPerSecOut
ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPerSecOut.description: The average output bytes/sec over last 4 seconds. These are bytes processed by this policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesIn.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesIn
ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesIn.description: The number of bytes ingress. These are bytes ingress to policy before being processed by policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPassed.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPassed
ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesPassed.description: The number of bytes passed. These are bytes processed by the policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesDropped.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesDropped
ltmBwcPolicyStatBytesDropped.description: The number of bytes dropped. These are bytes dropped by the policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatPacketsIn.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatPacketsIn
ltmBwcPolicyStatPacketsIn.description: The number of packets ingress. These are packets input to the policy processing.

ltmBwcPolicyStatPacketsPassed.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatPacketsPassed
ltmBwcPolicyStatPacketsPassed.description: The number of packets passed. These are packets passed by the policy.

ltmBwcPolicyStatActivePolicies.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatActivePolicies
ltmBwcPolicyStatActivePolicies.description: The number of current policies. This is active number of current policies in system.

ltmBwcPolicyStatInactivePolicies.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatInactivePolicies
ltmBwcPolicyStatInactivePolicies.description: The number of inactive policies created. This is inactive number of policies in the system.

ltmBwcPolicyStatTotalPolicies.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatTotalPolicies
ltmBwcPolicyStatTotalPolicies.description: The number of total policies created. This is total number of policies in system.

ltmBwcPolicyStatTimeDataCollected.name: ltmBwcPolicyStatTimeDataCollected
ltmBwcPolicyStatTimeDataCollected.description: The time since start in seconds. This is the time since the stats information has been collected.
