ltmDnsQueryFilterNumber.description: The number of ltmDnsQueryFilter entries in the table.

ltmDnsQueryFilterTable.name: ltmDnsQueryFilterTable
ltmDnsQueryFilterTable.description: A table containing information of DNS query type filtering.

ltmDnsQueryFilterName.name: ltmDnsQueryFilterName
ltmDnsQueryFilterName.description: The name of a DNS security profile.

ltmDnsQueryFilterIndex.name: ltmDnsQueryFilterIndex
ltmDnsQueryFilterIndex.description: The index of DNS query type filter for the specified DNS security profile.

ltmDnsQueryFilterType.name: ltmDnsQueryFilterType
ltmDnsQueryFilterType.description: The DNS query type value that is either included or excluded depending on the query_type_inclusion flag. Value 0 (no) implies disable (exclusion) and 1 (yes) is enable (inclusion).

ltmDnsHeaderFilterNumber.name: ltmDnsHeaderFilterNumber
ltmDnsHeaderFilterNumber.description: The number of ltmDnsHeaderFilter entries in the table.

ltmDnsHeaderFilterTable.name: ltmDnsHeaderFilterTable
ltmDnsHeaderFilterTable.description: A table containing information of DNS header opcode filtering.

ltmDnsHeaderFilterName.name: ltmDnsHeaderFilterName
ltmDnsHeaderFilterName.description: The name of a DNS security profile.

ltmDnsHeaderFilterIndex.name: ltmDnsHeaderFilterIndex
ltmDnsHeaderFilterIndex.description: The index of DNS header opcode exclusion for the specified DNS security profile.

ltmDnsHeaderFilterOpcodeExclusion.name: ltmDnsHeaderFilterOpcodeExclusion
ltmDnsHeaderFilterOpcodeExclusion.description: The DNS header opcode values. Value of 3 is not used.

ltmLsnPrefixNumber.name: ltmLsnPrefixNumber
ltmLsnPrefixNumber.description: The number of ltmLsnPrefix entries in the table.

ltmLsnPrefixTable.name: ltmLsnPrefixTable
ltmLsnPrefixTable.description: A table containing information of LSN prefix.

ltmLsnPrefixName.name: ltmLsnPrefixName
ltmLsnPrefixName.description: The name of a LSN prefix node.

ltmLsnPrefixAddrType.name: ltmLsnPrefixAddrType
ltmLsnPrefixAddrType.description: The IP address type of ltmLsnPrefixAddr.

ltmLsnPrefixAddr.name: ltmLsnPrefixAddr
ltmLsnPrefixAddr.description: The IP address of a node. It is interpreted within the context of a ltmLsnPrefixAddrType value.

ltmLsnPoolNumber.name: ltmLsnPoolNumber
ltmLsnPoolNumber.description: The number of ltmLsnPool entries in the table.

ltmLsnPoolTable.name: ltmLsnPoolTable
ltmLsnPoolTable.description: A table containing information of LSN pool.

ltmLsnPoolName.name: ltmLsnPoolName
ltmLsnPoolName.description: The name of a LSN Pool.

ltmLsnPoolMemberCount.name: ltmLsnPoolMemberCount
ltmLsnPoolMemberCount.description: The total number of members in the specified pool.

ltmLsnPoolRouteAdvertisement.name: ltmLsnPoolRouteAdvertisement
ltmLsnPoolRouteAdvertisement.description: Specifies whether route advertisement is enabled or disabled for translated IP addresses.

ltmLsnPoolMode.name: ltmLsnPoolMode
ltmLsnPoolMode.description: NAPT mode provides standard address and port translation allowing multiple clients to share the same external address. Deterministic mode provides address and port translations that can be consistently reversed so that external address and port combinations can identify specific clients.

ltmLsnPoolPersistenceMode.name: ltmLsnPoolPersistenceMode
ltmLsnPoolPersistenceMode.description: Persistence settings for LSN translation entries. none: Specifies that there is no persistence for the translation. address: Specifies that the translation reuses the port mapping for subsequent packets sent from the same internal IP address and port to the same external IP address while the mapping is still active, regardless of the external port. addressPort: Specifies that the translation reuses the port mapping for subsequent packets sent from the same internal IP address and port to the same external IP address and port while the mapping is still active.

ltmLsnPoolPersistenceTimeout.name: ltmLsnPoolPersistenceTimeout
ltmLsnPoolPersistenceTimeout.description: Maximum time-to-live for inactive translation entries.

ltmLsnPoolPersistencePrefixLengthIpv4.name: ltmLsnPoolPersistencePrefixLengthIpv4
ltmLsnPoolPersistencePrefixLengthIpv4.description: Deprecated! This field is removed. Number of significant bits in the client IPv4 address to be used as the persistence key.

ltmLsnPoolPersistencePrefixLengthIpv6.name: ltmLsnPoolPersistencePrefixLengthIpv6
ltmLsnPoolPersistencePrefixLengthIpv6.description: Deprecated! This field is removed. Number of significant bits in the client IPv6 address to be used as the persistence key.

ltmLsnPoolInboundConnections.name: ltmLsnPoolInboundConnections
ltmLsnPoolInboundConnections.description: If true, will enable inbound connections to translation addresses and ports.

ltmLsnPoolIcmpEcho.name: ltmLsnPoolIcmpEcho
ltmLsnPoolIcmpEcho.description: If true, will enable icmp-echo requests for translation addresses.

ltmLsnPoolTranslationPortRangeLow.name: ltmLsnPoolTranslationPortRangeLow
ltmLsnPoolTranslationPortRangeLow.description: Specifies the low end of the range of port numbers available for use with translation IP addresses.

ltmLsnPoolTranslationPortRangeHigh.name: ltmLsnPoolTranslationPortRangeHigh
ltmLsnPoolTranslationPortRangeHigh.description: Specifies the high end of the range of port numbers available for use with translation IP addresses.

ltmLsnPoolClientConnectionLimit.name: ltmLsnPoolClientConnectionLimit
ltmLsnPoolClientConnectionLimit.description: Specifies the maximum number of simultaneous translated connections a client or subscriber is allowed to have. A value of zero signifies no limit.

ltmLsnPoolEgressInterfacesEnabled.name: ltmLsnPoolEgressInterfacesEnabled
ltmLsnPoolEgressInterfacesEnabled.description: If true, source address translation is allowed on the interfaces specified in the egress-interfaces list.

ltmLsnPoolLogPublisher.name: ltmLsnPoolLogPublisher
ltmLsnPoolLogPublisher.description: Specifies the name of the log publisher that logs translation events, if any.

ltmLsnPoolHairpinMode.name: ltmLsnPoolHairpinMode
ltmLsnPoolHairpinMode.description: If enabled, will enable hairpinning for inbound connections. A hairpin connection between two subscribers goes through the NAT device and uses translation addresses so that it appears to each subscriber that the other is an external host.

ltmLsnPoolLogProfile.name: ltmLsnPoolLogProfile
ltmLsnPoolLogProfile.description: Specifies the name of the log profile that control the logging of translation events, if any.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolNumber.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolNumber
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolNumber.description: The number of ltmLsnPrefixLsnPool entries in the table.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolTable.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolTable
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolTable.description: A table containing information of LSN pool prefix.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolLsnPrefixName.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolLsnPrefixName
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolLsnPrefixName.description: The name of a LSN prefix node.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolLsnPoolName.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolLsnPoolName
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolLsnPoolName.description: The name of a LSN pool.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddressType.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddressType
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddressType.description: The IP address type of ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddress.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddress.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddress
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddress.description: The IP address of a node. It is interpreted within the context of a ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolPrefixAddressType value.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupNumber.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupNumber
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupNumber.description: The number of ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackup entries in the table.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupTable.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupTable
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupTable.description: A table containing information of LSN pool backup prefix.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupLsnPrefixName.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupLsnPrefixName
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupLsnPrefixName.description: The name of a LSN prefix node.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupLsnPoolName.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupLsnPoolName
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupLsnPoolName.description: The name of a LSN pool.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddressTy.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddressType
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddressTy.description: The IP address type of ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddress.

ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddress.name: ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddress
ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddress.description: The IP address of a node. It is interpreted within the context of a ltmLsnPrefixLsnPoolBackupPrefixAddressType value.

ltmLsnPoolVlanNumber.name: ltmLsnPoolVlanNumber
ltmLsnPoolVlanNumber.description: The number of ltmLsnPoolVlan entries in the table.

ltmLsnPoolVlanTable.name: ltmLsnPoolVlanTable
ltmLsnPoolVlanTable.description: A table containing VLAN information of LSN pool.

ltmLsnPoolVlanLsnPoolName.name: ltmLsnPoolVlanLsnPoolName
ltmLsnPoolVlanLsnPoolName.description: The name of a LSN pool.

ltmLsnPoolVlanVlanName.name: ltmLsnPoolVlanVlanName
ltmLsnPoolVlanVlanName.description: The name of VLAN for LSN pool.

ltmLsnPoolStatResetStats.name: ltmLsnPoolStatResetStats
ltmLsnPoolStatResetStats.description: The action to reset resetable statistics data in ltmLsnPoolStat. Setting this value to 1 will reset statistics data. Note, some statistics data may not be reset including data that are incremental counters.

ltmLsnPoolStatNumber.name: ltmLsnPoolStatNumber
ltmLsnPoolStatNumber.description: The number of ltmLsnPoolStat entries in the table.

ltmLsnPoolStatTable.name: ltmLsnPoolStatTable
ltmLsnPoolStatTable.description: A table containing statistic information of LSN pool.

ltmLsnPoolStatName.name: ltmLsnPoolStatName
ltmLsnPoolStatName.description: The name of a LSN Pool.

ltmLsnPoolStatHairpinConnectionRequests.name: ltmLsnPoolStatHairpinConnectionRequests
ltmLsnPoolStatHairpinConnectionRequests.description: The number of hairpin connection requests. A hairpin connection between two subscribers goes through the NAT device and uses translation addresses so that it appears to each subscriber that the other is an external host.

ltmLsnPoolStatActiveHairpinConnections.name: ltmLsnPoolStatActiveHairpinConnections
ltmLsnPoolStatActiveHairpinConnections.description: The number of active hairpin connections. A hairpin connection between two subscribers goes through the NAT device and uses translation addresses so that it appears to each subscriber that the other is an external host.

ltmLsnPoolStatTranslationRequestFailures.name: ltmLsnPoolStatTranslationRequestFailures
ltmLsnPoolStatTranslationRequestFailures.description: The number of translation request failures.

ltmLsnPoolStatPersistenceMappingFailures.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPersistenceMappingFailures
ltmLsnPoolStatPersistenceMappingFailures.description: The number of persistence mapping translation request failures.

ltmLsnPoolStatHairpinConnectionFailures.name: ltmLsnPoolStatHairpinConnectionFailures
ltmLsnPoolStatHairpinConnectionFailures.description: The number of failed hairpin connections. A hairpin connection failure occurs when a subscriber connects to an inbound reservation but a connection could not be created.

ltmLsnPoolStatBackupPoolTranslations.name: ltmLsnPoolStatBackupPoolTranslations
ltmLsnPoolStatBackupPoolTranslations.description: The number of translation requests that were served using the backup pool.

ltmLsnPoolStatLogFailures.name: ltmLsnPoolStatLogFailures
ltmLsnPoolStatLogFailures.description: The number of logging attempts that resulted in failure.

ltmLsnPoolStatTotalEndPoints.name: ltmLsnPoolStatTotalEndPoints
ltmLsnPoolStatTotalEndPoints.description: The product of the number of IP addresses and the translation port range. This is computed when the pool membership or translation port range changes.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceRequests.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceRequests
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceRequests.description: The total number of PCP Announce requests received.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceResponsesUcast.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceResponsesUcast
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceResponsesUcast.description: The total number of unicast PCP Announce responses transmitted.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceResponsesMultic.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceResponsesMulticast
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpAnnounceResponsesMultic.description: The total number of multicast PCP Announce responses transmitted.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpMapRequests.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpMapRequests
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpMapRequests.description: The total number of PCP Map requests received.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpMapResponses.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpMapResponses
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpMapResponses.description: The total number of PCP Map responses transmitted.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpPeerRequests.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpPeerRequests
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpPeerRequests.description: The total number of PCP Peer requests received.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpPeerResponses.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpPeerResponses
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpPeerResponses.description: The total number of PCP Peer responses transmitted.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsInvalidRequest.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsInvalidRequest
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsInvalidRequest.description: The total number of invalid or malformed PCP requests received.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsUnavailableResour.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsUnavailableResource
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsUnavailableResour.description: The total number of PCP requests received where the server has insufficient resources to complete the requested operation.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsNotAuthorized.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsNotAuthorized
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsNotAuthorized.description: The total number of PCP requests that generated (or caused) an unauthorized error when attempting to create a mapping.

ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsOther.name: ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsOther
ltmLsnPoolStatPcpErrorsOther.description: The total number of PCP requests received that resulted in other errors.

ltmLsnPoolStatActivePortBlocks.name: ltmLsnPoolStatActivePortBlocks
ltmLsnPoolStatActivePortBlocks.description: The total number of port blocks actively in use.

ltmLsnPoolStatActiveClientsReachedLimit.name: ltmLsnPoolStatActiveClientsReachedLimit
ltmLsnPoolStatActiveClientsReachedLimit.description: Total clients who have reached the max port blocks allocated to them.

ltmLsnPoolStatActiveZombiePortBlocks.name: ltmLsnPoolStatActiveZombiePortBlocks
ltmLsnPoolStatActiveZombiePortBlocks.description: Total blocks which have reached their lifetime and cannot be used for new allocations. They are not yet deleted because there are connections using ports in that block.

ltmLsnPoolStatTotalClientsReachedLimit.name: ltmLsnPoolStatTotalClientsReachedLimit
ltmLsnPoolStatTotalClientsReachedLimit.description: Total client connections rejected because client hit client-block-limit and could not find any free ports in the existing blocks.

ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlocksCreat.name: ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlocksCreated
ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlocksCreat.description: Total blocks which have reached their lifetime and cannot be used for new allocations. They are not yet deleted because there are connections using ports in that block.

ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlocksDelet.name: ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlocksDeleted
ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlocksDelet.description: Total zombie blocks deleted after their zombie timeouts. When a zombie block is deleted, the connections using them are killed.

ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlockConnec.name: ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlockConnectionsKilled
ltmLsnPoolStatTotalZombiePortBlockConnec.description: Total connections killed due to zombie block reaching zombie timeout.

ltmSpdyProfileNumber.name: ltmSpdyProfileNumber
ltmSpdyProfileNumber.description: The number of ltmSpdyProfile entries in the table.

ltmSpdyProfileTable.name: ltmSpdyProfileTable
ltmSpdyProfileTable.description: A table containing information about the SPDY profile.

ltmSpdyProfileName.name: ltmSpdyProfileName
ltmSpdyProfileName.description: The name of a SPDY profile.

ltmSpdyProfileConfigSource.name: ltmSpdyProfileConfigSource
ltmSpdyProfileConfigSource.description: The state that specifies whether this is a base/pre-configured profile or user defined profile.

ltmSpdyProfileDefaultName.name: ltmSpdyProfileDefaultName
ltmSpdyProfileDefaultName.description: The name of the profile from which the specified profile derives its attribute default values.

ltmSpdyProfileActivationMode.name: ltmSpdyProfileActivationMode
ltmSpdyProfileActivationMode.description: The manner in which SPDY connections are made. npn - TLS Extension, Next Protocol Negotiation is used to decide which SPDY protocol is used. always - All connections will be assumed to be SPDY connections. Clients that only support HTTP will not be supported.

ltmSpdyProfilePriorityHandling.name: ltmSpdyProfilePriorityHandling
ltmSpdyProfilePriorityHandling.description: The manner in which streams of different priorities are handled. strict - Higher priority streams will be processed to completion before lower priority streams are processed. fair - Higher priority streams will use more bandwidth than lower priority streams without completely blocking the lower priority streams.

ltmSpdyProfileInsertHeader.name: ltmSpdyProfileInsertHeader
ltmSpdyProfileInsertHeader.description: The state indicating whether or not an HTTP header that indicates the use of SPDY should be inserted into the request going to the back-end server.

ltmSpdyProfileInsertHeaderName.name: ltmSpdyProfileInsertHeaderName
ltmSpdyProfileInsertHeaderName.description: The HTTP header inserted into the request going to the back-end server, if that functionality is enabled.

ltmSpdyProfileConcurrentStreamsPerConnec.name: ltmSpdyProfileConcurrentStreamsPerConnection
ltmSpdyProfileConcurrentStreamsPerConnec.description: The maximum amount of concurrent streams allowed per connection.

ltmSpdyProfileConnectionIdleTimeout.name: ltmSpdyProfileConnectionIdleTimeout
ltmSpdyProfileConnectionIdleTimeout.description: The amount of time, in seconds, a connection is open idly before it is shutdown.

ltmSpdyProfileReceiveWindow.name: ltmSpdyProfileReceiveWindow
ltmSpdyProfileReceiveWindow.description: Specifies the size of the receive window in kilobytes. The receive window is a mechanism to stall individual upload streams when needed. This mechanism is only available for SPDY version 3 connections.

ltmSpdyProfileFrameSize.name: ltmSpdyProfileFrameSize
ltmSpdyProfileFrameSize.description: Specifies the size of the data frames, in bytes, that SPDY will send to the client. Larger frame sizes will improve network utilization, but may affect concurrency.

ltmSpdyProfileWriteSize.name: ltmSpdyProfileWriteSize
ltmSpdyProfileWriteSize.description: Specifies the total size of combined data frames, in bytes, SPDY will send in a single write. This controls the size of the TLS records when SPDY is used over SSL. A large write size will cause SPDY to buffer more data, but will improve network utilization.

ltmSpdyProfileCompressionLevel.name: ltmSpdyProfileCompressionLevel
ltmSpdyProfileCompressionLevel.description: Specifies the amount of compression to do by default for the headers of the specified profiles. The compression level must be between 0 and 10. Higher numbers correspond to more compression.

ltmSpdyProfileCompressionWindowSize.name: ltmSpdyProfileCompressionWindowSize
ltmSpdyProfileCompressionWindowSize.description: Specifies the size of the compression window for the specified profiles in kilobytes. The compression window size must be between 1 and 128 kilobytes.

ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsNumber.name: ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsNumber
ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsNumber.description: The number of ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersions entries in the table.

ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsTable.name: ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsTable
ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsTable.description: A table containing information on the supported SPDY protocol versions.

ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsName.name: ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsName
ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsName.description: The name of a SPDY profile.

ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsIndex.name: ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsIndex
ltmSpdyProfileProtocolVersionsIndex.description: The index of the protocol versions used to determine which SPDY versions are supported and in what order those versions should be prioritized when deciding which version to use.
